584
00:44:20,210 --> 00:44:23,330
Got any plans to get married?

585
00:44:24,800 --> 00:44:27,160
- Are you matchmaking me?
- You're not getting my daughter.

586
00:44:27,350 --> 00:44:29,360
- Don't want her.
- What'd you say?

587
00:44:29,360 --> 00:44:30,660
She's 12, isn't she?

588
00:44:31,693 --> 00:44:32,560
Mm.

589
00:44:40,600 --> 00:44:41,970
What is this about?

590
00:44:44,376 --> 00:44:45,516
Togawa,

591
00:44:47,030 --> 00:44:48,040
do you like Kyoto?

592
00:44:50,960 --> 00:44:51,880
What?

593
00:45:23,270 --> 00:45:24,260
I'm home.

594
00:45:25,490 --> 00:45:26,600
Sorry I'm late.

595
00:45:35,320 --> 00:45:36,593
Let's hurry up and make dinner

596
00:45:36,618 --> 00:45:37,586
so we can eat it.

597
00:45:37,640 --> 00:45:38,360
Oh.

598
00:45:39,510 --> 00:45:40,320
Ah.

599
00:45:41,570 --> 00:45:42,850
I knew it.

600
00:45:46,580 --> 00:45:48,150
It's better to eat you first.

601
00:45:51,910 --> 00:45:53,040
It's cold.

602
00:45:53,680 --> 00:45:54,660
Ah...

603
00:45:56,440 --> 00:45:57,720
What's wrong with you?

604
00:45:58,880 --> 00:46:00,080
You seem off…

605
00:46:01,080 --> 00:46:02,050
Mm.

606
00:46:03,560 --> 00:46:04,500
It's nothing.

607
00:46:06,080 --> 00:46:07,890
I'm just glad.

608
00:46:09,140 --> 00:46:10,400
Glad I met you.

609
00:46:23,380 --> 00:46:24,720
Shima? What's wrong?

610
00:46:29,400 --> 00:46:31,430
Are you crying?

611
00:46:34,800 --> 00:46:35,940
I'm not crying.

612
00:46:42,230 --> 00:46:43,880
You're right. Not crying.

613
00:46:46,840 --> 00:46:47,650
But...

614
00:46:49,560 --> 00:46:50,770
You look like you're about to.

615
00:47:17,940 --> 00:47:20,440
- Is that so?
- Mm. I also don't know.

616
00:47:20,610 --> 00:47:22,740
- Got it.
- Shima.

617
00:47:24,133 --> 00:47:25,333
Let's go get lunch.

618
00:47:27,990 --> 00:47:29,190
I already bought it.

619
00:47:29,700 --> 00:47:31,160
Then take it with you.

620
00:47:33,140 --> 00:47:34,120
No thank you.

621
00:47:34,840 --> 00:47:36,920
If you don't hurry, I'm eating it.

622
00:47:40,520 --> 00:47:41,670
Where are we going?

623
00:47:41,940 --> 00:47:43,200
Somewhere nice.

624
00:47:48,840 --> 00:47:50,360
So what's so nice about this place?

625
00:47:50,980 --> 00:47:53,730
It's nice, right? A city park.

626
00:47:56,920 --> 00:47:58,040
What about my cup ramen?

627
00:47:58,820 --> 00:47:59,890
What am I supposed to do?

628
00:48:00,450 --> 00:48:02,930
Yeah. What to do?

629
00:48:06,240 --> 00:48:07,440
Want my melon bread?

630
00:48:08,340 --> 00:48:09,430
No thanks.

631
00:48:11,620 --> 00:48:12,360
Ah.

632
00:48:21,190 --> 00:48:22,870
Why bring me all the way here?

633
00:48:31,570 --> 00:48:32,440
Shima.

634
00:48:35,040 --> 00:48:36,160
I...

635
00:48:39,570 --> 00:48:41,730
Ah, take it.

636
00:48:49,140 --> 00:48:51,270
- Here.
- Thanks, Uncle.

637
00:48:51,270 --> 00:48:53,200
- Wait. Call him big brother.
- Uncle?

638
00:48:53,200 --> 00:48:56,100
Nah, it's fine. I am almost 30.

639
00:48:56,260 --> 00:48:57,882
It's not strange for someone at this age

640
00:48:57,907 --> 00:48:58,913
to become a father.

641
00:48:59,680 --> 00:49:01,080
- Thanks!
- Mm.

642
00:49:05,940 --> 00:49:08,210
Try it.

643
00:49:08,310 --> 00:49:10,520
Ah, hey, hey.

644
00:49:11,380 --> 00:49:12,260
It's actually hard.

645
00:49:12,260 --> 00:49:14,960
- It's hard. You must juggle it high.
- You...

646
00:49:16,230 --> 00:49:18,690
Don't smile like you're going to cry.

647
00:49:20,200 --> 00:49:21,830
It's not cute at all.

648
00:49:24,100 --> 00:49:25,600
Because I'm a man.

649
00:49:27,030 --> 00:49:28,550
I'm not cute.

650
00:49:30,610 --> 00:49:31,360
Besides,

651
00:49:32,820 --> 00:49:34,840
I'm not cheerful like you.

652
00:49:37,000 --> 00:49:39,490
Shima, what's wrong?

653
00:49:41,400 --> 00:49:42,420
Sorry.

654
00:49:43,896 --> 00:49:45,576
I've got some things to take care of.

655
00:49:45,940 --> 00:49:47,010
I'll head back first.

656
00:49:52,050 --> 00:49:53,823
An executive from headquarters

657
00:49:53,848 --> 00:49:55,976
has his eye on you.

658
00:49:57,030 --> 00:49:59,156
Well, it's probably

659
00:49:59,170 --> 00:50:00,970
a good opportunity for you.

660
00:50:02,050 --> 00:50:03,960
No reason for you to turn it down…

661
00:50:08,744 --> 00:50:09,720
Ah, welcome back.

662
00:50:10,008 --> 00:50:10,808
You were quick.

663
00:50:11,848 --> 00:50:13,656
Where's Togawa-san?

664
00:50:15,832 --> 00:50:16,984
I came back first.

665
00:50:17,608 --> 00:50:18,328
Oh.

666
00:50:19,454 --> 00:50:20,414
Are you okay?

667
00:50:23,912 --> 00:50:24,840
You must have heard

668
00:50:27,240 --> 00:50:28,248
The matter of Togawa-san

669
00:50:29,144 --> 00:50:30,248
having to move branches.

670
00:50:36,552 --> 00:50:37,352
Huh?

671
00:50:40,280 --> 00:50:41,192
Huh?

672
00:50:46,040 --> 00:50:46,952
Could it be...

673
00:50:49,336 --> 00:50:50,520
that you didn't know?

674
00:50:53,144 --> 00:50:54,856
I'm sorry.

675
00:50:56,952 --> 00:50:57,752
No.

676
00:50:58,136 --> 00:50:59,704
I thought since you two left together,

677
00:50:59,731 --> 00:51:01,498
it would be something you'd talk about.

678
00:51:04,152 --> 00:51:05,144
Togawa-san.

679
00:51:06,504 --> 00:51:08,088
He said to disclose it.

680
00:51:09,067 --> 00:51:09,935
So I thought

681
00:51:10,472 --> 00:51:12,392
maybe he wanted to tell you personally.

682
00:52:05,928 --> 00:52:08,408
I'm just glad. Glad I met you.

683
00:52:29,384 --> 00:52:30,936
So he wants to end it, huh?

684
00:52:41,448 --> 00:52:43,128
Mm. Yes?

685
00:52:47,985 --> 00:52:48,721
Today...

686
00:52:50,306 --> 00:52:51,352
Can we meet?

687
00:53:16,440 --> 00:53:17,240
Did you wait long?

688
00:53:18,776 --> 00:53:19,512
No.

689
00:53:20,776 --> 00:53:21,784
I just got here.

690
00:53:22,936 --> 00:53:23,928
Haa...

691
00:53:25,304 --> 00:53:27,032
It's so rare

692
00:53:27,680 --> 00:53:28,826
you're actually saying,

693
00:53:28,851 --> 00:53:30,531
'I want to meet you.'

694
00:53:31,672 --> 00:53:33,096
I didn't say it like that.

695
00:53:36,048 --> 00:53:37,864
But you wanted to meet me, right?

696
00:53:41,224 --> 00:53:42,248
Yes,

697
00:53:45,048 --> 00:53:46,312
I did want to meet you.

698
00:54:02,136 --> 00:54:03,528
What's wrong with you?

699
00:54:04,968 --> 00:54:06,104
You're acting strange.

700
00:54:10,264 --> 00:54:11,432
When I thought this was the last time,

701
00:54:12,760 --> 00:54:14,360
I wanted to leave some feelings behind.

702
00:54:16,344 --> 00:54:17,288
Congratulations

703
00:54:18,344 --> 00:54:19,832
on your promotion.

704
00:54:23,080 --> 00:54:24,824
Thank you for everything.

705
00:54:26,600 --> 00:54:27,880
Thanks to you,

706
00:54:28,760 --> 00:54:30,408
I've had a pretty fun time.

707
00:54:32,728 --> 00:54:34,136
Is it hard for you to tell me?

708
00:54:35,368 --> 00:54:37,000
You don't have to worry too much.

709
00:54:37,912 --> 00:54:39,480
You can just say it...

710
00:54:50,616 --> 00:54:51,864
I like you.

711
00:54:55,560 --> 00:54:57,336
Is that really such a surprise?

712
00:54:58,310 --> 00:55:00,392
Did my actions not reach you at all?

713
00:55:04,088 --> 00:55:04,696
So why...

714
00:55:07,352 --> 00:55:08,856
Why are you saying this now?

715
00:55:09,160 --> 00:55:10,640
I wanted to say it, and I want to be

716
00:55:10,665 --> 00:55:11,740
with you from now on.

717
00:55:12,632 --> 00:55:13,656
What are you talking about?

718
00:55:15,320 --> 00:55:16,424
It's not going to be easy.

719
00:55:16,504 --> 00:55:18,232
You don't know that.

720
00:55:19,592 --> 00:55:20,392
Well...

721
00:55:23,170 --> 00:55:24,008
Togawa-san.

722
00:55:25,256 --> 00:55:26,408
Aren't you straight?

723
00:55:28,696 --> 00:55:29,496
Shima.

724
00:55:31,784 --> 00:55:32,856
I...

725
00:55:33,912 --> 00:55:35,976
think you're the cutest.

726
00:55:37,800 --> 00:55:39,176
Your past,

727
00:55:40,488 --> 00:55:43,064
- or that fact that you're gay.
- Ha...

728
00:55:44,264 --> 00:55:45,336
Are you pitying me?

729
00:55:46,408 --> 00:55:48,821
Whether it's love, pity, or whatever,

730
00:55:48,846 --> 00:55:50,101
it's all feelings.

731
00:55:51,464 --> 00:55:53,656
I feel very attached to you.

732
00:55:59,400 --> 00:56:00,952
So, how do you feel?

733
00:56:06,664 --> 00:56:08,232
If I have to be away from Togawa-san,

734
00:56:11,304 --> 00:56:12,824
to be honest, I'd be lonely.

735
00:56:14,600 --> 00:56:15,448
But...

736
00:56:17,720 --> 00:56:19,386
But, I've been thinking that continuing

737
00:56:19,393 --> 00:56:20,993
this kind of relationship is not good.

738
00:56:23,384 --> 00:56:25,656
It would be better to draw a clear line.

739
00:56:25,944 --> 00:56:26,760
What?

740
00:56:28,424 --> 00:56:29,704
I don't understand at all.

741
00:56:31,816 --> 00:56:34,120
Did you even hear what I said clearly?

742
00:56:34,440 --> 00:56:36,568
I told you I want to be with you.

743
00:56:36,968 --> 00:56:38,264
What I'm trying to say is that...

744
00:56:40,136 --> 00:56:41,769
Our relationship isn't that close to be

745
00:56:41,776 --> 00:56:43,462
in a long distance relationship.

746
00:56:46,712 --> 00:56:47,368
Then...

747
00:56:50,024 --> 00:56:52,216
You really want to end it like this?

748
00:56:54,056 --> 00:56:55,582
You can't say that we want to end it.

749
00:56:57,240 --> 00:56:58,136
It wasn't like

750
00:56:59,960 --> 00:57:01,446
we had anything from the beginning.

751
00:57:01,467 --> 00:57:02,528
Except for the sex...

752
00:57:02,552 --> 00:57:03,576
You...

753
00:57:07,560 --> 00:57:09,777
It's true, from the start,

754
00:57:09,805 --> 00:57:11,211
I didn't really like you,

755
00:57:13,125 --> 00:57:14,693
And then, I like you more and more

756
00:57:15,512 --> 00:57:18,744
- as I got to know you...
- Thank you.

757
00:57:20,312 --> 00:57:21,704
I'm happy,

758
00:57:23,608 --> 00:57:24,312
but...

759
00:57:27,176 --> 00:57:28,856
If you're just in a relationship with me

760
00:57:28,876 --> 00:57:30,242
out of temporary confusion,

761
00:57:32,504 --> 00:57:33,564
then maybe you should

762
00:57:33,571 --> 00:57:34,657
just get a bride already.

763
00:57:35,080 --> 00:57:35,896
Huh?

764
00:57:38,290 --> 00:57:39,624
What are you talking about?

765
00:57:43,416 --> 00:57:46,008
- If you long for a family...
- Huh?

766
00:57:49,368 --> 00:57:50,408
You have...

767
00:57:53,224 --> 00:57:54,680
been worried about that this whole time?

768
00:57:54,680 --> 00:57:56,888
Aren't you serious about it?

769
00:57:58,552 --> 00:57:59,752
I'm a man,

770
00:58:02,344 --> 00:58:04,568
so of course I can't have children.

771
00:58:05,704 --> 00:58:08,040
- It's a waste of time continuing this.
- Hey, listen first.

772
00:58:09,896 --> 00:58:11,592
Look this way.

773
00:58:15,016 --> 00:58:16,264
I also...

774
00:58:18,968 --> 00:58:21,592
- I'm hurt in my own way...
- Shima, look at me.

775
00:58:21,992 --> 00:58:24,456
Look at me properly! Look!

776
00:58:26,472 --> 00:58:27,384
Listen.

777
00:58:29,092 --> 00:58:30,360
"That kind of thing,"

778
00:58:31,992 --> 00:58:34,312
even if I didn't meet you,

779
00:58:34,790 --> 00:58:36,607
it's just a passing fancy that can
be easily thrown away.

780
00:58:36,632 --> 00:58:38,630
You certainly can't throw it away.

781
00:58:40,712 --> 00:58:42,200
My past...

782
00:58:42,856 --> 00:58:44,536
Your past...

783
00:58:45,688 --> 00:58:47,432
They're parts of us, right?

784
00:58:49,800 --> 00:58:52,264
With a past like yours,

785
00:58:53,304 --> 00:58:54,600
don't you think

786
00:58:56,344 --> 00:58:58,696
that I can never fulfill you.

787
00:58:59,688 --> 00:59:00,552
Besides...

788
00:59:01,336 --> 00:59:02,782
I was expecting us to be together

789
00:59:02,789 --> 00:59:03,902
until the end of our lives.

790
00:59:06,216 --> 00:59:06,936
So, if that's the case,

791
00:59:09,096 --> 00:59:10,242
it would have been better

792
00:59:10,256 --> 00:59:11,582
if nothing had ever happened.

793
00:59:16,536 --> 00:59:17,400
Enough already.

794
00:59:21,896 --> 00:59:22,696
Shima.

795
00:59:27,176 --> 00:59:28,309
It's true, your feelings

796
00:59:28,316 --> 00:59:29,522
are yours to have,

797
00:59:32,968 --> 00:59:34,388
but you don't have the right to

798
00:59:34,401 --> 00:59:36,054
trample on my feelings for you.

799
00:59:53,240 --> 00:59:54,920
I get everything now. Let's end it.

800
01:00:05,704 --> 01:00:06,520
Ah...

801
01:00:09,758 --> 01:00:11,736
Consider it as the last time...

802
01:00:19,400 --> 01:00:20,473
Apart from the sex,

803
01:00:20,493 --> 01:00:21,753
there was nothing, you said.

804
01:00:27,432 --> 01:00:28,598
You came here today with

805
01:00:28,623 --> 01:00:29,591
that in mind, right?

806
01:00:31,000 --> 01:00:32,664
To you, I was just that,

807
01:00:35,736 --> 01:00:37,656
weren't I?

808
01:00:43,368 --> 01:00:44,456
Get up!

809
01:01:06,696 --> 01:01:08,392
You're the most cruel.

810
01:01:12,536 --> 01:01:14,536
Are you telling me to resent my past?

811
01:02:04,952 --> 01:02:06,760
Am I being resented?

812
01:02:11,384 --> 01:02:12,776
If so...

813
01:02:18,360 --> 01:02:20,392
At least he won't forget me, right?

814
01:03:17,688 --> 01:03:18,488
Hey.

815
01:03:19,144 --> 01:03:20,712
Don't cry so much, guys.

816
01:03:21,176 --> 01:03:23,560
No, no, none of us are crying.

817
01:03:23,560 --> 01:03:24,888
Yeah, no one's crying.

818
01:03:25,032 --> 01:03:26,406
Liar! You voice was trembling

819
01:03:26,420 --> 01:03:27,860
just a second ago.

820
01:03:28,120 --> 01:03:30,856
Hey, why'd you have to say that?

821
01:03:34,200 --> 01:03:35,032
Oh well.

822
01:03:36,168 --> 01:03:37,432
Take care, everyone.

823
01:03:37,960 --> 01:03:39,126
I'll call you once in a while

824
01:03:39,151 --> 01:03:40,206
even after I go.

825
01:03:41,750 --> 01:03:42,977
Togawa-san,

826
01:03:43,164 --> 01:03:44,517
thank you for your hard work.

827
01:03:46,120 --> 01:03:47,192
Take care.

828
01:03:49,112 --> 01:03:50,376
I'll go to Kyoto.

829
01:03:51,048 --> 01:03:51,768
Mm.

830
01:03:52,088 --> 01:03:54,056
You mean that?

831
01:03:54,504 --> 01:03:55,624
Goodbye, Shima.

832
01:04:07,656 --> 01:04:08,920
Thank you for everything.

833
01:05:53,832 --> 01:05:55,320
It's been a month, huh?

834
01:05:55,752 --> 01:05:57,464
- Since Togawa-san went there.
- Huh?

835
01:05:59,544 --> 01:06:00,737
Section Chief, you must be

836
01:06:00,744 --> 01:06:01,856
having a rough time.

837
01:06:01,880 --> 01:06:03,983
Don't call that.
It sounds so old-fashioned.

838
01:06:04,008 --> 01:06:05,960
Togawa-san said the same thing.

839
01:06:07,800 --> 01:06:08,776
Good morning.

840
01:06:09,592 --> 01:06:10,856
- Good morning.
- Good morning.

841
01:06:10,904 --> 01:06:11,640
Good morning.

842
01:06:11,880 --> 01:06:13,032
You cut your hair.

843
01:06:14,728 --> 01:06:17,704
A bit. It was getting too long.

844
01:06:18,024 --> 01:06:18,936
Is that so?

845
01:06:21,544 --> 01:06:23,170
By the way, Shima-kun, do you have

846
01:06:23,191 --> 01:06:24,703
a business card from Estec?

847
01:06:25,048 --> 01:06:27,528
Umm... Yes.

848
01:06:27,640 --> 01:06:29,080
What a relief.

849
01:06:29,352 --> 01:06:30,452
I need to go there,

850
01:06:30,472 --> 01:06:32,048
but I don't know the address.

851
01:06:32,072 --> 01:06:33,384
- I'll get it for you.
- Mm.

852
01:06:43,176 --> 01:06:44,520
Mm. Thanks.

853
01:06:46,360 --> 01:06:47,704
Shinagawa?

854
01:07:09,624 --> 01:07:10,552
Shima-kun.

855
01:07:23,761 --> 01:07:25,160
Shima, are you okay?

856
01:07:25,160 --> 01:07:27,272
Umm... It seems like he has a headache.

857
01:07:47,432 --> 01:07:48,312
I'm sorry.

858
01:07:49,384 --> 01:07:50,616
I'll get back to work now.

859
01:07:51,192 --> 01:07:53,112
It's fine. You can leave for today.

860
01:07:57,336 --> 01:08:00,152
Before he left, Togawa-san told me

861
01:08:02,440 --> 01:08:06,216
to not leave you alone

862
01:08:07,448 --> 01:08:09,008
he said

863
01:08:09,195 --> 01:08:10,921
"because he thinks he can be alone."

864
01:08:14,888 --> 01:08:15,640
But

865
01:08:18,440 --> 01:08:20,269
I didn't need him to tell me that.

866
01:08:20,736 --> 01:08:21,769
I'll do it anyway.

867
01:08:24,584 --> 01:08:26,014
Even though it has a different meaning

868
01:08:26,021 --> 01:08:27,381
from Togawa-san,

869
01:08:27,704 --> 01:08:28,600
